                            <comment id="14055923" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 9 Jul 2014 07:52:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Kim,&lt;br/&gt;
I think the PropertyPermissions should be kept. The corresponding FilePermissions should be removed. (The policy files have both PropertyPermissions and FilePermissions for java.runtime.version and java.fullversion. Since they are properties, the file permissions don&apos;t make sense, but the property permissions do.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
